{"name": "linear-tsv", "metadata": {"name": "linear-tsv", "version": "1.1.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5"], "home_page": "https://github.com/solidsnack/tsv", "license": "Apache", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Line-oriented, tab-separated value format", "upload_time": 1516442731}, "documentation": [""], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tsv", "documentation": ["coding: utf-8"], "functions": [{"name": "tsv.un", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "source", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "wrapper", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "error_bad_lines", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parse a text stream to TSV\n\nIf the source is a string, it is converted to a line-iterable stream. If\nit is a file handle or other object, we assume that we can iterate over\nthe lines in it.\n\nThe result is a generator, and what it contains depends on whether the\nsecond argument is set and what it is set to.\n\nIf the second argument is set to list, the default, then each element of\nthe result is a list of strings. If it is set to a class generated with\nnamedtuple(), then each element is an instance of this class, or None if\nthere were too many or too few fields.\n\nAlthough newline separated input is preferred, carriage-return-newline is\naccepted on every platform.\n\nSince there is no definite order to the fields of a dict, there is no\nconsistent way to format dicts for output. To avoid the asymmetry of a\ntype that can be read but not written, plain dictionary parsing is\nomitted."]}, {"name": "tsv.is_namedtuple", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.parse_lines", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "lines", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.parse_line", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "line", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.check_line_consistency", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "columns", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "values", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "line_no", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "error_bad_lines", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.parse_field", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "s", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.to", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "items", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "output", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Present a collection of items as TSV\n\nThe items in the collection can themselves be any iterable collection.\n(Single field structures should be represented as one tuples.)\n\nWith no output parameter, a generator of strings is returned. If an output\nparameter is passed, it should be a file-like object. Output is always\nnewline separated."]}, {"name": "tsv.format_collection", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "col", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.format_fields", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fields", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.format_field", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.escape_special_chars", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "s", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "tsv.escapes", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "tsv.FinalBackslashInFieldIsForbidden", "bases": ["ValueError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.reader", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "tsv.reader.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tsvfile", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.reader.__iter__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.reader.__next__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "tsv.reader.dialect", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.writer", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "tsv.writer.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tsvfile", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.writer.writerow", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "row", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.writer.writerows", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rows", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "tsv.writer.dialect", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "tsv.DictReader", "bas